Avalanches, landslides and floods havekilled almost 100 people since the start of the year in theSoviet Transcaucasian republic of Georgia, the official dailySotsialisticheskaya Industriya said.    Some 16,000 people have been left homeless and 80,000hectares of arable land and plantations rendered useless, thenewspaper said. The figures are still preliminary, but itestimated total losses at over 300 mln roubles.    It said a large number of livestock and birds were killedin the natural disaster and more than 1,800 km of roads neededrepairing. REUTER&#3;